 2020-08852020-11-11,  ,  ,  GAC,  , 
ActOther Than Statutory Authority
PrecisAppointment of MARK BERMAN to be High Commissioner for Canada in the Co-operative Republic of Guyana and as Plenipotentiary Representative of Canada to the Caribbean Community; CHRISTINA BUCHAN to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Zimbabwe, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Angola and as High Commissioner for Canada in the Republic of Botswana, with residence in Harare; LILIAN CHATTERJEE to be High Commissioner for Canada in the Commonwealth of Dominica, with residence in Bridgetown; BENOÎT-PIERRE LARAMÉE to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of the Congo, with residence in Kinshasa; JEANNETTE MENZIES to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Iceland; ADRIAN NORFOLK to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of the Sudan; and GILES NORMAN to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Serbia, with concurrent accreditation as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of North Macedonia and as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to Montenegro, with residence in Belgrade.
AttachmentsAttachment
